\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12386321 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6637546\charrsid4489010 Well when - naturally enough - when I was - sixteen - I had a special
 friend, my cousin, and - we used to - go out every - nearly every night and Sundays - enjoy in ourself. Chatting up the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7806616 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6637546\charrsid4489010 Where would you go, was this sort of local, you went round about walking?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12386321 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6637546\charrsid4489010 It - it - oh up Bucknall is a place what we
 used to call Maccaboney. This was a beautiful walk, we used to - oh we was - oh we did do some walking. And - we joined the - joined amateur dramatic society, but - my friend suffered with an impediment in his speech and so we had to leave that. I - I jo
ined that, thought it'd - it'd take the impediment out of his speech, but it didn't. Well - when he sung - when he sung he never - never - you couldn't - tell. But when he talked it was there. Marvellous thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7806616 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6637546\charrsid4489010 So you'd chat up the girls and you'd belong to the amateur dramatic society?

